table_caption: Global efficiency of network in LBP. rsFC data was used to compile binary undirected networks for each resting state network that had been thresholded within a network density range of 15%-30% in steps of 2.5%. The corresponding global efficiency scores for each network rsFC matrix were averaged across thresholds. A Wilcoxon rank-sum test was used to assess the statistical significance and the corresponding z values recorded. (* = p < 0.05, uncorrected).
